# рЯПФпЄП Image вЖТ Height Map вЖТ Normal Map вЖТ 3D Terrain Mesh

> Transform any flat 2D image into a fully exportable 3D terrain mesh and tangent-space normal map вАФ using pure Python and open-source libraries.

---

## рЯУЄ What It Does

| Input :Any `.png` / `.jpg` / `.bmp` image 
| output :`terrain.obj` вАФ 3D mesh (Blender, Unity, Unreal ready)

| Bright pixels вЖТ high elevation 
|`normal_map.png` вАФ RGB-encoded surface normals 
| Dark pixels вЖТ low elevation 
|Live 3D matplotlib preview 

| **No input file?** 

The script auto-generates a demo terrain with hills and noise so you can see the full pipeline immediately.

---

## рЯЧЇпЄП Pipeline Overview

```
Input Image (any photo)
        вФВ
        вЦЉ
 Luminance Extraction

    gray = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_RGB2LAB) 

        |
        вЦЉ
 Gaussian Smoothing  вФАвФАвЖТ  Height Map
 (removes noise/spikes)
        вФВ
        вФЬвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФАвФР
        вЦЉ                         вЦЉ
 Sobel Gradient               Grid of XYZ vertices
 вИВh/вИВx,  вИВh/вИВy                X = col / (cols-1)
        вФВ                      Y = row / (rows-1)
        вЦЉ                      Z = np.power(hmap,gamma)*HEIGHT_SCALE
 N = (вИТвИВh/вИВx, вИТвИВh/вИВy, 1)              вФВ
 normalise вЖТ unit vector               вЦЉ
        вФВ                    Quad Triangulation
        вЦЉ                    2 triangles per cell
  normal_map.png              terrain.obj  +  UV map
```

