## рЯЪА Quick Start

```bash
# Run with the auto-generated demo terrain
python terrain_mesh_generator.py

# Run with your own image
# вЖТ place your image in the same folder, then set INPUT_IMAGE in the script
python terrain_mesh_generator.py input.png
```

**Outputs appear in the same folder as the script:**
```
terrain_mesh_generator.py
terrain.obj          вЖР 3D mesh
normal_map.png       вЖР normal map
```

---

## рЯОЫпЄП Configuration

Open `terrain_mesh_generator.py` and edit the constants at the top:

```python
INPUT_IMAGE   = "input.png"   # path to your source image
OUTPUT_MESH   = "terrain.obj" # output 3D mesh filename
OUTPUT_NORMAL = "normal_map.png"  # output normal map filename

MESH_WIDTH    = 128    # grid columns  (64 = fast/blocky ¬Ј 512 = detailed/slow)
MESH_HEIGHT   = 128    # grid rows
HEIGHT_SCALE  = 20.0   # max elevation (5 = subtle ¬Ј 50 = dramatic mountains)
SMOOTH_SIGMA  = 1.5    # blur radius   (0 = off ¬Ј 3.0 = smooth rolling hills)
```

| Parameter | Low value | High value |
|---|---|---|
| `MESH_WIDTH/HEIGHT` | 64 вЖТ fast, coarse | 512 вЖТ slow, detailed |
| `HEIGHT_SCALE` | 5 вЖТ flat terrain | 50 вЖТ tall mountains |
| `SMOOTH_SIGMA` | 0 вЖТ spiky/raw | 3.0 вЖТ smooth hills |

